    • 方法详细资料

      • add

        void add(T data)
        Add the data as a leaf in the BST. Should traverse the tree to find the appropriate location. If the data is already in the tree, then nothing should be done (the duplicate shouldn't get added, and size should not be incremented). Should have a running time of O(log n) for a balanced tree, and a worst case of O(n).
        参数:
        data - the data to be added
        抛出:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the data is null

      • remove

        T remove(T data)
        Removes the data from the tree. There are 3 cases to consider: 1: the data is a leaf. In this case, simply remove it. 2: the data has one child. In this case, simply replace it with its child. 3: the data has 2 children. There are generally two approaches: replacing the data with either the largest element that is smaller than the element being removed (commonly called the predecessor), or replacing it with the smallest element that is larger than the element being removed (commonly called the successor). For this assignment, use the predecessor. You may use iteration to find/remove the predecessor AFTER you have found the node to be removed recursively (but don't start back at the root to do so). We recommend you find and remove the predecessor recursively, but there is not penalty for doing so iteratively for this assignment. Should have a running time of O(log n) for a balanced tree, and a worst case of O(n).
        参数:
        data - the data to remove from the tree.
        返回:
        the data removed from the tree. Do not return the same data that was passed in. Return the data that was stored in the tree.
        抛出:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the data is null
        java.util.NoSuchElementException - if the data is not found

      • get

        T get(T data)
        Returns the data in the tree matching the parameter passed in (think carefully: should you use .equals or == ?). Should have a running time of O(log n) for a balanced tree, and a worst case of O(n).
        参数:
        data - the data to search for in the tree.
        返回:
        the data in the tree equal to the parameter. Do not return the same data that was passed in. Return the data that was stored in the tree.
        抛出:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the data is null
        java.util.NoSuchElementException - if the data is not found

      • contains

        boolean contains(T data)
        Returns whether or not data equivalent to the given parameter is contained within the tree. Should have a running time of O(log n) for a balanced tree, and a worst case of O(n).
        参数:
        data - the data to search for in the tree.
        返回:
        whether or not the parameter is contained within the tree.
        抛出:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the data is null

      • size

        int size()
        Should run in O(1).
        返回:
        the number of elements in the tree

      • levelorder

        java.util.List<T> levelorder()
        Generate a level-order traversal of the tree. To do this, add the root node to a queue. Then, while the queue isn't empty, remove one node, add its data to the list being returned, and add its left and right child nodes to the queue. If what you just removed is null, ignore it and continue with the rest of the nodes. Should run in O(n).
        返回:
        a level order traversal of the tree

      • listLeavesDescending

        java.util.List<T> listLeavesDescending()
        Creates a list of all leaf nodes present in the tree in descending order. Should run in O(n).
        返回:
        a list of all leaf nodes in descending order

      • clear

        void clear()
        Clear the tree. Should be O(1).

      • height

        int height()
        Calculate and return the height of the root of the tree. A node's height is defined as max(left.height, right.height) + 1. A leaf node has a height of 0 and a null child should be -1. Should be calculated in O(n).
        返回:
        the height of the root of the tree, -1 if the tree is empty

        THIS METHOD IS ONLY FOR TESTING PURPOSES. DO NOT USE IT IN YOUR CODE DO NOT CHANGE THIS METHOD
        返回:
        the root of the tree
